Designed to work with gnome-terminal set to use a customized version of the
White On Black schema, with Text color set to #E6E1DC and Background color
set to #2B2B2B, and the Tango palette selected.

Remember to symlink vimrc into position, e.g.

	cd $HOME && ln -s .vim/vimrc .vimrc

Command-T requires some compilation, and doesn't like being linked against a
different version of ruby from the one against which Fedora's vim-enhanced was
linked. e.g.

	cd bundle/command-t && rvm 1.8.7 rake make
